Title: qs.parse allows ReDoS via attacker-controlled RegExp delimiter option
Category: regex-dos
Severity: medium
Description: The public `parse` API accepts an `options.delimiter` value that may be either a string or a RegExp. In `lib/parse.js`, `parseValues()` performs `cleanStr.split(options.delimiter, limit)` directly on attacker-influenced input, with no validation or sandboxing of the supplied regular expression. If an application exposes delimiter customization to untrusted input or plugs in a user-controlled RegExp, an attacker can supply a catastrophic-backtracking regex and cause CPU exhaustion during parsing.
Request: node - <<'NODE'
const qs = require('/tmp/pwnkit-audit-36282a3d/node_modules/qs');
const s='x'.repeat(500000);
for (const re of [/(x+)+y/, /(x|xx)+y/]) {
  const t=Date.now();
